    entryRequirements: 'Level 4 Entry(Year 1 courses) Engineering (Math and Science). Qualifications needed: Diploma + Transcript (all pages) + translation only for Non-Latin languages countries (Minimum 32 UCAS POINTS). For Pre-settlement status - requires 3 years of residency proof.',
    documentsRequired: 'Passport/ID, Diploma + Transcript (all pages) + translation only for Non-Latin languages countries (Minimum 32 UCAS POINTS), Personal Statement (400 words), Share Code (Start with "S", original email - PDF), Proof of address (no older than 3 months like Bank statement, Mobile or Utility bill, Rental agreement contract, Payslips, GP or NHS letters). For Pre-settlement requires one document as a proof for each year (e.g., 2019 Bank statement, 2020 payslip and 2021 NHS letter). SFE SCREENSHOT PROOF, Selfie, EduForYou Consent Form (Signed digitally by Student), Course page details (SLC), Page 42 from PN1 form (Only for undergraduate courses, completed and signed by student Digitally or Printed).',
    interviewInfo: 'Online. The admin asks the agents to request additional available days from the student and then forwards these options to Regent. The student will receive an email confirming one of the selected options. After that, the admin uploads the Teams link to the platform, which the student can click to join the interview. Students can be booked for interview only once the Maths and Science test is passed. After passing the math and science test, the student will be scheduled for an interview (online).',
