    personalStatementGuidelines: '400 words - NO AI',
    additionalInfo: 'Timetable: 50% online - 50% on campus. One day online and one day on campus during the week from 9AM to 6PM. Two evenings online and 2 evenings on campus from 6PM to 9PM. Two evenings from 6PM to 9PM and one full day of the weekend from 9AM to 6PM. WEEKEND Option: Fri & Sat from 9AM to 6PM if available or the above evening combine with weekend if available. ALL TIMETABLES ARE LIMITED AND NO SPACES ARE GUARANTEED. NO FULL WEEKEND TIMETABLES AVAILABLE BECAUSE NO MAINTENANCE LOAN AVAILABLE. If you have students who are happy with only weekend, they must be happy that they will not receive maintenance loan, and WE REQUIRE A MINIMUM 20 STUDENTS TO RUN THE CLASS. Internally, for students requiring SFE approval, you cannot receive an upfront commission. This will be paid together with the final commission. If the student is denied SFE but has attended classes, they will be required to pay the amount according to the signed payment plan. If a student does not receive the entitlement letter from SFE within two weeks of the course start date, they will be deferred to the next intake.',
